President Biden and Prime Minister Suga of Japan held a discussion on various policy issues and global challenges. They emphasized the importance of the U.S.-Japan alliance and its role in promoting peace and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region. The leaders also reaffirmed the United States' commitment to defending Japan, including the Senkaku Islands, under the security treaty. They addressed regional security concerns such as China and North Korea, advocating for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and the resolution of the abductions issue. Additionally, they pledged to collaborate on tackling the COVID-19 pandemic, addressing climate change, and advancing shared values, global security, and prosperity.